article.headline: N. Dakota St. 77, Wis.-Milwaukee 69
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- Mike Nelson scored 22 points and Brett Winkelman 15 as North Dakota State defeated Wisconsin-Milwaukee 77-69 Saturday night. The Bison (21-6), playing in their first ESPN Bracket Buster game, also got 12 points from Ben Woodside. For the Panthers (15-12), James Eayrs and Ricky Franklin scored 14 points each, Deonte Roberts and Avery Smith had 11 each and Tone Boyle had 10. The Bison led 18-8 after a 3-pointer by Josh Vaughan. Milwaukee fought back to lead 21-20 on a basket by Deonte Roberts but Nelson came right back with a basket to put North Dakota on top for good in the game at 22-21. North Dakota State led 34-31 at the half. Winkelman's basket with 12:01 left ended a 10-0 run to open the second half that put the Bison up 44-31.
